PCP2CREMax_T1T2Map_Analysis

Hari Rallapalli

introduction

Presented below are revised analyses of the PCP2CREMax data as suggested by Brian. There are three significant changes made to the analyses after our meeting:

  1. Reference ROIs have been added to the analyses

  2. I directly test for significant differences in PCL R1 between DT and NoDT animals. I am using the package “lmerTest” instead of “lme4” to get these p-values, as suggested by Brian

  3. I corrected the Group-wise R1 histograms by random effects (correcting for inter-mouse variance).

my_unnest <- tidyr::unnest
errorfunc <- function(x) {
m <- mean(x)
u <- m + sd(x)
l <- m - sd(x)
return(data.frame(ymin=l, ymax=u, y=m))
}


remove_outliers <- function(x, na.rm = TRUE, ...) {
  qnt <- quantile(x, probs=c(.25, .75), na.rm = na.rm, ...)
  H <- 1.5 * IQR(x, na.rm = na.rm)
  y <- x
  y[x < (qnt[1] - H)] <- NA
  y[x > (qnt[2] + H)] <- NA
  y
}

numextract <- function(string){
  unlist(regmatches(string,gregexpr("[[:digit:]]+\\.*[[:digit:]]*",string)))
}

strcorrect <- function(x){
  x %>% noquote() %>% gsub(", ",",",.) %>% gsub("\\[|\\]", "", .) %>% gsub("[\r\n]", "", .) %>% str_split(.," ")
}

All animals across all experiments included here

gf <- read.csv("G:\\MINCVM\\PCLKO\\PCP2-DTR\\results\\MAPPING_RESULTS_2021-03-25_23_37_24.csv", header = TRUE, stringsAsFactors = FALSE, col.names = c("V1" = "Filenames", "V2" = "PCL", "V3" = "WM", "V4" = "ML", "V5" = "IGL", "V6" = "Reference")) %>%
  mutate(mouse = str_extract(Filenames, "PCP2CREMax_B\\d+_\\w\\d*"),
         maptype = "T1") %>% 
  group_by(mouse) %>%
  mutate(toxin = ifelse(str_detect(mouse,"_C"),"NoDT","DT"),
         batch = str_extract(mouse,"B\\d")) %>%
  mutate(PCL = sapply(PCL,strcorrect),
         WM = sapply(WM,strcorrect),
         ML = sapply(ML,strcorrect),
         IGL = sapply(IGL,strcorrect),
         Reference = sapply(Reference,strcorrect)) %>%
  gather(roi,measurement,PCL,WM,ML,IGL,Reference) %>% 
  unnest() %>%
  mutate(measurement = 1000/as.numeric(measurement)) %>%
  arrange(mouse) %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  ungroup()

gf %>% group_by(toxin) %>%
  summarize(n=n_distinct(mouse)) %>%
  kable() %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped", "hover", "condensed"))

creating one-hot dummy variables for toxin and roi

dmy <- gf %>%
  mutate(roi = as.factor(roi),
         toxin = as.factor(toxin)) %>%  
  dummyVars(~ toxin + roi, data = .)

model_gf <- data.frame(predict(dmy, newdata = gf))
model_gf <- model_gf %>%
  mutate(measurement = gf$measurement,
         mouse = gf$mouse,
         batch = gf$batch)

Linear modeling

model <- model_gf %>% 
  lmer(measurement ~ toxin.DT:roi.IGL + roi.IGL + 
         toxin.DT:roi.ML + roi.ML +
         toxin.DT:roi.PCL + roi.PCL +
         toxin.DT:roi.WM + roi.WM +
         toxin.DT:roi.Reference + roi.Reference -1 + (1|mouse),data=.)

model_summary <- model %>% summary()

Batch effects

As we discussed, Batch 2 data seem anomalous. There are experimental design considerations that warrant excluding these data from further analysis.

gf <- merge(gf, random_effects,by='mouse',all.x = TRUE)

gf <- gf %>% mutate(corrected_measurements = measurement - randeff)

random effects correction of group-wise R1 histograms

gf_means_Corrected <- gf %>% filter(batch != "B2") %>%
  mutate(R1.measurements = corrected_measurements) %>%
  group_by(toxin,roi) %>%
  summarise(Mean = mean(R1.measurements))

GroupWise_R1_FilterB2_ByLabel_Corrected <- gf %>% filter(batch != "B2") %>%
  mutate(R1.measurements = corrected_measurements) %>%
  ggplot() + 
  aes(x=R1.measurements, y=..ncount.., color = toxin, fill = toxin) + 
  geom_vline(data = gf_means_Corrected, aes(xintercept = Mean, color = toxin, alpha = 0.75)) +
  geom_freqpoly(bins = 30) +
  facet_wrap(~roi, scales = "free") +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0.5,1.5)) +
  xlab("R1 Estimate (1/sec)") +
  ylab(label = "Normalized counts") +
  guides(alpha = FALSE) +
  plottheme +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank())
